      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ رَجُلٌ مَاتَ وَ عَلَيْهِ صَوْمٌ يُصَامُ عَنْهُ أَوْ يُتَصَدَّقُ قَالَ \"يُتَصَدَّقُ عَنْهُ فَإِنَّهُ أَفْضَلُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4322 - It is narrated from Muhammad ibn Isma'il ibn Bazee' that he said:\nI asked Abu Ja'far al-Thani (as) about a man who died and had fasting obligations upon him. Should fasting be done on his behalf, or should charity be given on his behalf?\nImam (as) said: \"Charity should be given on his behalf, for it is better.\""
        ]
      }
    },
